    Folder Lock without any S/W

    Open Notepad and copy the below code and save as locker.bat. At first time start it will create folder with Locker automatically for u. Don't forget to change your password in the code its shown the place where to type your password.
    after creation of Locker folder again click on the locker.bat.it will ask.press Y then Locker folder will be disappeared.again to get it click on locker.bat. and give ur password u will get the folder again.

    ****************************************
    ******************



    cls
    @ECHO OFF
    title Folder Locker
    if EXIST "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}" goto UNLOCK
    if NOT EXIST Locker goto MDLOCKER
    :CONFIRM
    echo Are you sure u want to Lock the folder(Y/N)
    set/p "cho=>"
    if %cho%==Y goto LOCK
    if %cho%==y goto LOCK
    if %cho%==n goto END
    if %cho%==N goto END
    echo Invalid choice.
    goto CONFIRM
    :LOCK
    ren Locker "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    attrib +h +s "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    echo Folder locked
    goto End
    :UNLOCK
    echo Enter password to Unlock folder
    set/p "pass=>"
    if NOT %pass%==type your password here goto FAIL
    attrib -h -s "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    ren "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}" Locker
    echo Folder Unlocked successfully
    goto End
    :FAIL
    echo Invalid password
    goto end
    :MDLOCKER
    md Locker
    echo Locker created successfully
    goto End
    :End

    to lock a folder.......... create a *.bat file containing

     

    ren foldername foldername.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}

     

    save it in directory where the folder is

     

     

    to unlock a folder......... create a *.bat file containing

     

    ren foldername.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D} foldername

     

    save it in directory where the folder is

     

    enjoy

    My version in português (Portugal - PT):


    cls
    @ECHO OFF
    title Proteger o directorio
    if EXIST "MyProtectFolder.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}" goto UNLOCK
    if NOT EXIST MyProtectFolder goto MDLOCKER
    :CONFIRM
    echo Queres mesmo proteger o directorio (s/n)?
    set/p "cho=>"
    if %cho%==S goto LOCK
    if %cho%==s goto LOCK
    if %cho%==N goto END
    if %cho%==n goto END
    echo Opcao invalida.
    goto CONFIRM
    :LOCK
    ren MyProtectFolder "MyProtectFolder.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    attrib +h +s "MyProtectFolder.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    echo Directorio protegido
    goto End
    :UNLOCK
    echo Introduza a password para desbloquear o directorio
    set/p "pass=>"
    if NOT %pass%==mypassword goto FAIL
    attrib -h -s "MyProtectFolder.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    ren "MyProtectFolder.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}" MyProtectFolder
    echo Directorio desbloqueado
    goto End
    :FAIL
    echo Password invalida
    goto end
    :MDLOCKER
    md MyProtectFolder
    echo Directorio criado
    goto End
    :End


    If your folder have a name diferent that "MyProtectFolder", you have to change every word that you find with the name "MyProtectFolder" to your folder name prefer.

    You can change the address     {21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D} to one of this:

    My Computer: {20D04FE0-3AEA-1069-A2D8-08002B30309D}
    Recycle Bin: {645FF040-5081-101B-9F08-00AA002F954E}
    Control Panel: {21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}
    Printers: {2227A280-3AEA-1069-A2DE-08002B30309D}
    Internet Explorer: {871C5380-42A0-1069-A2EA-08002B30309D}
    Network Neighborhood: {208D2C60-3AEA-1069-A2D7-08002B30309D}
    Subscriptions: {F5175861-2688-11d0-9C5E-00AA00A45957}
    ActiveX Cache Folder: {88C6C381-2E85-11D0-94DE-444553540000}

    I tested and works perfect.

    cls
    @ECHO OFF
    title Folder Locker
    if EXIST "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}" goto UNLOCK
    if NOT EXIST Locker goto MDLOCKER
    :CONFIRM
    echo Are you sure u want to Lock the folder(Y/N)
    set/p "cho=>"
    if %cho%==Y goto LOCK
    if %cho%==y goto LOCK
    if %cho%==n goto END
    if %cho%==N goto END
    echo Invalid choice.
    goto CONFIRM
    :LOCK
    ren Locker "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    attrib +h +s "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    echo Folder locked
    pause
    goto End
    :UNLOCK
    echo Enter password to Unlock folder
    set/p "pass=>"
    if NOT %pass%==password goto FAIL
    attrib -h -s "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    ren "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}" Locker
    echo Folder Unlocked successfully
    goto End
    :FAIL
    echo Invalid password
    goto end
    :MDLOCKER
    md Locker
    echo Locker created successfully
    pause
    goto End
    :End

    ::::::

    What is actually done here is simply renaming the folder. You can see th 'REN' command in the code. the actual folder is reflected to some system folders when locked.

    ren Locker "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"

    Unlocking means renaming back to the normal name

    ren "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}" Locker

    ::It is very simple Muhammad,

    ::I'll show you my script, it requires a password both ways (My preferred method)...

    ::I will HIGHLIGHT where you should change the password.

    ::I will also BOLD AND ITALICIZE where you can change the name of the folder.

    ::(Make sure to change the password BEFORE "locking" the file, AND do not try to

    ::type the script with actual bolds, underlines, and italics...)

    ::On top of that, i made it possible for you to just copy and paste this onto a notepad for kicks

    ::and giggles. It will run perfectly.


    cls
    @ECHO OFF
    title Folder nameoffolder
    if EXIST "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}" goto UNLOCK
    if NOT EXIST nameoffolder goto MDLOCKER
    :CONFIRM
    echo Input password to proceed with locking.
    set/p "pass=>"
    if %pass%== password goto LOCK
    echo Incorrect Password.
    goto CONFIRM
    :LOCK
    ren nameoffolder "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    attrib +h +s "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    echo Folder locked
    goto End
    :UNLOCK
    echo Enter password to unlock folder
    set/p "pass=>"
    if NOT %pass%== password goto FAIL
    attrib -h -s "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    ren "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}" nameoffolder
    echo Folder Unlocked successfully
    goto End
    :FAIL
    echo Invalid password
    goto end
    :MDLOCKER
    md nameoffolder

    echo nameoffolder created successfully
    goto End
    :End

    ::There are only two places where you need to change your password.  Ideally,

    ::if you really wanted to, you could make a password to unlock, and one to lock

    ::I hope this helps everyone. Remember, for someone who knows script, I would change this

    ::file into an exe

    ::This tip was brought to you by R3-4M (Reform)

    Hey made a little change so that when you unlock the folder and run it again it will lock the pre-existing folder instead of having to lock an entirely different folder.... enjoy!

    cls
    @echo off
    title Folder Locker
    IF EXIST "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B303­09D}" GOTO UNLOCK
    IF EXIST "LOCK" GOTO LOCKK
    IF NOT EXIST Locker GOTO MDLOCKER
    echo Folder Created.
    :CONFIRM
    echo Are you sure you want to lock the folder? (Y/N)
    set/p "cho="
    IF %cho%==Y GOTO LOCK
    IF %cho%==y GOTO LOCK
    IF %cho%==N GOTO END
    IF %cho%==n GOTO END
    echo Invalid Choice.
    GOTO CONFIRM
    :LOCK
    ren Locker "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B303­09D}"
    attrib +h +s "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B303­09D}"
    echo Folder Locked.
    GOTO END

    :UNLOCK
    echo Enter password to unlock the Folder :
    set/p "pass="
    IF NOT %pass% == YourPassword GOTO FAIL
    attrib -h -s "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B303­09D}"
    ren "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B303­09D}" LOCK
    echo Folder Unlocked Successfully.
    GOTO END
    :FAIL
    echo Invalid Password!
    GOTO END

    :MDLOCKER
    md Locker
    echo Folder created.

    :LOCKK
    ren LOCK "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B303­09D}"
    attrib +h +s "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B303­09D}"
    echo Folder Locked.
    GOTO END

    GOTO END
    :END
    PAUSE

    ANOTHER SAFER WAY:

    1. Generate a very long password, e.g. 1024 letters; **THIS IS IMPORTANT, ELSE OTHERS MAY GUESS THE PASSWORD
    2. Save in a text file called key.txt
    3. Write the batch file as usual, but CHANGE THIS LINE
        set /p pass="pass=>"
       TO THIS LINE
        set /p pass=<%~dp0\key.txt
       OR MAYBE
        set /p pass=<%~dp0key.txt
    4. Save the batch file AND USE bat to exe converter to convert it.
    5. That's all!

    Folder Lock without any S/W

    Open Notepad and copy the below code and save as locker.bat. At first time start it will create folder with Locker automatically for u. Don't forget to change your password in the code its shown the place where to type your password.
    after creation of Locker folder again click on the locker.bat.it will ask.press Y then Locker folder will be disappeared.again to get it click on locker.bat. and give ur password u will get the folder again.

    ****************************************
    ******************



    cls
    @ECHO OFF
    title Folder Locker
    if EXIST "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}" goto UNLOCK
    if NOT EXIST Locker goto MDLOCKER
    :CONFIRM
    echo Are you sure u want to Lock the folder(Y/N)
    set/p "cho=>"
    if %cho%==Y goto LOCK
    if %cho%==y goto LOCK
    if %cho%==n goto END
    if %cho%==N goto END
    echo Invalid choice.
    goto CONFIRM
    :LOCK
    ren Locker "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    attrib +h +s "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    echo Folder locked
    goto End
    :UNLOCK
    echo Enter password to Unlock folder
    set/p "pass=>"
    if NOT %pass%==type your password here goto FAIL
    attrib -h -s "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    ren "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}" Locker
    echo Folder Unlocked successfully
    goto End
    :FAIL
    echo Invalid password
    goto end
    :MDLOCKER
    md Locker
    echo Locker created successfully
    goto End
    :End

    Version 2. More secure and simple. After 8 years I updated it to 2.o, then 2.1 and 2.2 today!

    @echo off
    title Folder Locker v2
    echo FOLDER LOCKER! Updated by Daniil Shatilov!
    echo Enter the name of folder to lock/unlock it!
    :menu
    set /p folder=Name:
    echo Lock or unlock? (l\u)
    :ln
    set /p lockun=
    if %lockun% == l goto lock
    if %lockun% == u goto unlock
    echo L or u.
    goto ln

    :lock
    IF EXIST "%folder%"\pass.lock goto lockno
    echo Lock the folder? (y\n)
    :lockyesno
    set /p folderlock=?:
    if %folderlock% == y goto lockok
    if %folderlock% == n goto menu
    echo Y or n.
    goto lockyesno

    :lockok
    md "%folder%"
    echo Place files in folder now.
    start "%folder%"
    pause
    echo Enter password for folder!
    set /p passlock=Password:

    ECHO %passlock% >> "%folder%"\pass.lock
    echo Password successfully entered.
    attrib +h +s "%folder%"
    echo Folder Locked! 
    goto menu

    :unlock
    IF NOT EXIST "%folder%" goto notexist
    echo Unlock the folder with password, please!
    set /p passreal=<"%folder%"\pass.lock
    :passunlock
    set /p passunlock=Password: 
    IF %passunlock% == %passreal% goto unlocking
    echo Wrong password!
    goto passunlock

    :unlocking
    attrib -h -s "%folder%"
    echo Folder unlocked! 
    pause
    goto menu

    :notexist
    echo Folder doesn't exist. 
    pause
    goto lock

    :lockno
    echo Folder already locked!
    pause
    goto unlock

    this is NOT something i have created....was just combining some codes which i have found via inter net and for me it is working with a mask characters when typing the password....the password for this bat file is 'test'.....hope u find it helpful..!!!

    CLS

    @ECHO OFF
    title coolhacking-tricks.blogspot.com
    if EXIST "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}" goto UNLOCK
    if NOT EXIST MyFolder goto MDMyFolder
    :CONFIRM
    echo Are you sure to lock this folder? (Y/N)
    set/p "cho=>"
    if %cho%==Y goto LOCK
    if %cho%==y goto LOCK
    if %cho%==n goto END
    if %cho%==N goto END
    echo Invalid choice.
    goto CONFIRM
    :LOCK
    ren MyFolder "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    attrib +h +s "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    echo Folder locked
    goto End
    :UNLOCK
    powershell -Command $pword = read-host "Enter password to Unlock Your Secure Folder" -AsSecureString ; ^
        $BSTR=[System.Runtime.InteropServices.Marshal]::SecureStringToBSTR($pword) ; ^
            [System.Runtime.InteropServices.Marshal]::PtrToStringAuto($BSTR) > .tmp.txt 
    set /p pass=<.tmp.txt & del .tmp.txt
    if NOT %pass%== test goto FAIL
    attrib -h -s "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}"
    ren "Control Panel.{21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D}" MyFolder
    echo Folder Unlocked successfully
    goto End
    :FAIL
    echo Invalid password
    goto end
    :MDMyFolder
    md MyFolder
    echo MyFolder created successfully
    goto End
    :End

    echo Invalid password
    goto end
    :MDLOCKER
    md Locker
    echo Locker created successfully
